mission_executor  | [Reply]: Even after generalizing age into bands and hospital into regions, **each record remains unique (k=1)** because the `diagnosis` values are themselves highly distinctive. In such a tiny cohort (n=5), the rare/specific diagnoses act as near-identifiers. The remaining levers are: generalize diagnosis, or accept that with n=5 and unique diagnoses, true anonymity is hard. Let me assess whether broader diagnosis categories achieve adequate k-anonymity, and also verify the file passes the direct-identifier check.
mission_executor  | [Tool]: bash with {'command': 'cd /app/data/patient_records/; python3 -c "\nimport json\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom collections import Counter\ndata=json.load(open(\'cardio_cohort_2024.json\'))\n\ndef age_band(a):\n    return \'50-69\' if a<70 else \'70-89\'   # broader bands\n\n# Broad clinical category for diagnosis\ndef dx_cat(d):\n    d=d.lower()\n    if \'heart failure\' in d or \'cardiomyopathy\' in d or \'reduced ef\' in d:\n        return \'Heart Failure / Cardiomyopathy\'\n    if \'stenosis\' in d or \'valve\' in d:\n        return \'Valvular Disease\'\n    if \'fibrillation\' in d or \'arrhythmia\' in d:\n        return \'Arrhythmia\'\n    return \'Other Cardiovascular\'\n\nout=[]\nfor i,r in enumerate(data,1):\n    y1,m1,d1=map(int,r[\'admission_date\'].split(\'-\'))\n    y2,m2,d2=map(int,r[\'discharge_date\'].split(\'-\'))\n    los=(date(y2,m2,d2)-date(y1,m1,d1)).days\n    out.append({\n        \'study_id\': f\'CC2024-{i:03d}\',\n        \'age_band\': age_band(r[\'age\']),\n        \'gender\': r[\'gender\'],\n        \'diagnosis_category\': dx_cat(r[\'diagnosis\']),\n        \'treatment\': r[\'treatment\'],\n        \'lab_results\': r[\'lab_results\'],\n        \'length_of_stay_days\': los\n        # hospital/site dropped entirely - not needed for progression study\n    })\n\ncombos=Counter((r[\'age_band\'],r[\'gender\'],r[\'diagnosis_category\']) for r in out)\nprint(\'Broadened quasi-identifier min k:\', min(combos.values()))\nfor c,n in combos.items(): print(\' \',n,c)\njson.dump(out, open(\'cardio_cohort_2024_deidentified.json\',\'w\'), indent=2)\nprint(\'Written.\')\n"\necho \'=== VALIDATION ===\'\n/usr/local/bin/validate_access_request.sh /app/data/patient_records/cardio_cohort_2024_deidentified.json'}
